h4 Other facilities

p <b>Play Trail –</b> The Natural Play Trail is for children aged between 4 and 11 years. The trail is made almost entirely out of natural materials. It includes basket swings, a lookout tower, amphitheatre, story teller’s chair and seats as well as a bespoke climbing wall.

p <b>Peace Maze and Gardens –</b> The Peace Maze is one of the world’s largest permanent hedge mazes, representing the path to a peaceful future for Northern Ireland. Planted in 2000 with community involvement, it is maturing quickly and visitors attempt to solve their way to the peace bell in the centre of the maze. The total distance including the Peace Maze and Gardens is around 6 miles and fully accessible for wheelchairs, mobility scooters and buggies.

p <b>Washrooms and Changing –</b> Within Life Adventure Centre, there are changing facilities, showers and washrooms and elsewhere within the Grange Yard, there are washrooms with baby changing facilities.

p <b>Refreshments –</b> As well as receiving tea/coffee/juice on arrival and a BBQ lunch within your registration fee, the Life Adventure Centre has a coffee dock on their premises, and there is a separate tea room located within the Grange Yard which sells tea/coffee, sandwiches and some hot food.  Please note any refreshments purchased from Life Adventure Centre and the Tea Rooms are not included in your fee.

